      • BIOMETRIC_ENROLLED

        public static final RegistrationAttributes BIOMETRIC_ENROLLED
        The flag to indicate whether any biometric is enrolled.

        Prior to Android 10 (Q), only fingerprint integration is supported.

        For Android 10, fingerprint and face authentication is supported. Other forms of biometric authentication (e.g. Iris) could be supported during customization.

      • getAllAttributeValues

        public static java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String> getAllAttributeValues​(@NonNull
                                                                                               android.content.Context context,
                                                                                               boolean namesInSnakeCase)
        Returns all attribute values, except the TENANT_IDENTIFIER.

        If the attributes are going to send to IBM Security Verify Access, their names need to be in 'snake case' format (namesInSnakeCase = true).

        The TENANT_IDENTIFIER needs to be manually added before the request is submitted to IBM Security Verify Access. It can not be added here, because a new TENANT_IDENTIFIER value is created for each OnPremiseAuthenticator instance and stored in shared preferences. After registration, the TENANT_IDENTIFIER is available in OnPremiseAuthenticator.getIdentifier().

        Parameters:
        context - the context of the application.
        namesInSnakeCase - a flag indicating whether the attribute names should be in 'snake case' format (lowercase and underscore between words).
        Returns:
        hash map representing the attribute name and value.
